I'll post my thoughts in order!

Woah, woah there buddy. Those are some HUGE paragraphs and you need to rip and tear them down to size.

Dialogue is generally split up into their separate paragraphs for different characters. So:
>Careful not to draw too much attention I moved closer and whispered into his ear. “Relax Anon, this is just Maraza customs and I am sure there is a reason why…”. He interrupted me quickly. “What kind of garbage is this ? Do you see that weapon ? Close combat against the Zumio ?

Becomes
>Careful not to draw too much attention I moved closer and whispered into his ear. “Relax Anon, this is just Maraza customs and I am sure there is a reason why…”
>He interrupted me quickly. “What kind of garbage is this ? Do you see that weapon ? Close combat against the Zumio ? (...)"

I'll go a little more in-depth into dialogue, but I'm not a writer, so make sure to read some more elsewhere.
If your dialogue ends in a period, you don't need to add one outside the quotations. This also goes with ellipsis.
I would put a dash for an interruption instead of ellipsis, because the latter usually implies a trailing off and not a sudden cut.
Also you can change this period in
>Careful not to draw too much attention I moved closer and whispered into his ear.
Into a comma, because the whisper part works like if you put the whisper after the dialogue. It's a speech tag.

There's this weird thing you have here with shifting narrators. At the start it's this person with anon, right, got it, their memories, first person, but then
>The other passengers, multiple species all around with you and Anon as the only humans, seem to do so as well, quickly walking past.
It switches to second making the protagonist the reader. Keep this consistent, one or the other.

Cont.
